                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#3v">f. 3v</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note preceeded by the list of the individuals (the
                              relatives of the donor).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#3v">3v</locus>: ... ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡ ዘወኀበቶ፡ ወለተ፡
                              ገብርኤል፡ ስመ፡ አቡሃ፡ ተስፋ፡ ማርያም፡ ኀገረ፡ ህሤ፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#3v">3v</locus>: This is a book [belonging to the
                              church] of ʾabuna Mamas, which was donated by Walatta Gabrǝʾel, whose
                              father’s name is Tasfā Māryām, [of] Ḫagärä Hǝśe.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#140rb">f. 140rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#140rb">140rb</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡ ሀገረ፡ ህሴ፡
                              ዘወሀበቶ፡ ወለተ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ስመ፡ አቡሃ፡ ተስፋ፡ ማርያም፡ ከመ፡ {ይኩና፡} መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡
                              ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ አሜን፨</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#140rb">140rb</locus>: This is the book of (the church
                              of) ʾabuna Mamas of Hagärä Hǝse donated by Walatta Gabrǝʾel, whose
                              father’s name is Tasfā Māryām so that it might be for her a guide to
                              the Kingdom of Heaven. He who stole it or erased (its text) shall be
                              excommunicated. Amen.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#140rb">f. 140rb</locus>
                           <desc>: List of the names.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> By recent hand, in pen. The note enumerates several persons,
                              including the donor of the Ms. and her father. The list is not fully
                              identical to that of Additio 1. In violet ink. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>: The title is crudely
                           written on the front board: መፅሃፈ፡ ቅዳሴ 
 - <locus target="#10r">10r</locus>, 10v (in the bottom margin): Crude notes.
 - <locus target="#10v">10v</locus>, 42r, 42v, 43r, 44v, 45v, 48r, 49r, 50r (in
                           the upper margin): Crude notes.
 - <locus target="#141v">141v</locus>: Notes (number 16, referring to the number of quires in the
                           Ms., written once in Ethiopic and twice in European digits).
 -
                              <locus target="#142v">142v</locus>: Notes, in pink ink (pen
                           trials?).</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Coloured threads are inserted in the corners of
                              some fols. for navigating in the text.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
